6–1402","1320–Male":"1320–Deceased","1330–1380":"1330–1380","before 1376":"before 1376","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","about 1352":"about 1352","1339":"1339","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Moyne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  Norman, English: nickname from Old French  <i>moine</i>, Anglo-Norman French  <i>muine</i>,  <i>moingne</i> ‘monk’. Some of the following early bearers without the definite article could alternatively belong with (2).","2  English:  see  Moon   (1)."],"variants":[{"name":"Moin","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of <b>Moyne</b>, a nickname from Old French <i>moine</i>, Anglo-Norman French <i>muine</i>, <i>moingne</i> ‘monk’.","Muslim (mainly the Indian subcontinent): unexplained."]},{"name":"Moon","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Mohan  .","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Moyon in La Manche. Compare   Mounce  .","Americanized form of German   Mohn   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]},{"name":"Moynan","meanings":["Irish: perhaps a diminutive of   Moyne   or a reduced form of   Moynihan  ."]},{"name":"Moine","meanings":["French: from <i>moine</i> ‘monk’, probably applied as an occupational name for a servant at a monastery or an ironic nickname for someone of monkish behavior or appearance. Compare   Lemoine  ."]},{"name":"Moynes","meanings":["English: variant of   Moyne   with post-medieval excrescent  <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Moyne I was born about 1352, in Surrey, England, his father, William Le Moyne of Powderich II, was 34 and his mother, Lady Margery Merton, was 23. He married Mrs. Henry Moyne I before 1376. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1376, in his hometown, at the age of 25."},"et":{"about 1352–1376":"umbes 1352–1376","1352–1376":"1352–1376","1360–1404":"1360–1404","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1354–Female":"1354–Surnud","1376–1402":"1376–1402","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1330–1380":"1330–1380","before 1376":"enne 1376","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","about 1352":"umbes 1352","1339":"1339","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1352–1376":"noin 1352–1376","1352–1376":"1352–1376","1360–1404":"1360–1404","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1354–Female":"1354–Kuollut","1376–1402":"1376–1402","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1330–1380":"1330–1380","before 1376":"ennen vuotta 1376","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1402":"1402","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","about 1352":"noin 1352","1339":"1339","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1352–1376":"environ 1352–1376","1352–1376":"1352–1376","1360–1404":"1360–1404","1362–Female":"1362–Décédée","1354–Female":"1354–Décédée","1376–1402":"1376–1402","1320–Male":"1320–Décédé","1330–1380":"1330–1380","before 1376":"avant 1376","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","140